('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:b8935e2f', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Complete: ‘Mi móvil no ___ bien hoy.’ (doesn’t work well today)", "options": ["funciona", "funcionando", "carga", "conecta"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The conjugated present-tense form is needed: funciona. funcionando wrongly uses the gerund; carga/conecta are the wrong verb entirely."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:a00aa225', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘to connect’?", "options": ["conectar", "cargar", "guardar", "funcionar"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "conectar = to connect. The others are real tech verbs (to charge, to save, to work) but not this one."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:de4546ed', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"Hay un retraso en la aplicación.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. What is the problem?", "options": ["There is a delay in the app", "There is a new app available", "The app has been deleted", "The app is very fast today"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘hay un retraso’ = there is a delay/lag. The traps invent an unrelated update, deletion or speed."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:3227be45', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which is the correct Spanish for ‘video game’?", "options": ["el videojuego", "la videojuega", "el video juego", "los videojuego"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "el videojuego is one word, masculine, singular. The others wrongly change the gender ending, split it into two words, or use a plural article with a singular noun."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:7fb6ba6e', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which phrase means ‘to save photos’?", "options": ["guardar fotos", "subir fotos", "descargar fotos", "buscar fotos"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "guardar fotos = to save photos. subir (upload), descargar (download) and buscar (search for) are all real, easily confused tech verbs."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:814d6dbd', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Complete: ‘Uso la nube para ___ mis fotos.’ (to save)", "options": ["guardar", "guardando", "guardo", "guardado"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘para’ is always followed by the infinitive: guardar. guardando/guardo/guardado are the gerund, conjugated and past-participle forms."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:9a136f09', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘incredible’?", "options": ["increíble", "especial", "último", "siguiente"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "increíble = incredible. especial (special), último (last) and siguiente (next) are real opinion/sequence words, but different meanings."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:f27f7aae', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which phrase means ‘a benefit of technology’?", "options": ["un beneficio de la tecnología", "una ventaja de la tecnología", "una creación de la tecnología", "un impacto de la tecnología"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "beneficio = benefit. ventaja (advantage), creación (creation) and impacto (impact) are all real, similar abstract nouns used about technology."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:cb9d0592', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which phrase means ‘a minute’?", "options": ["un minuto", "una hora", "un día", "una semana"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "un minuto = a minute. hora (hour), día (day) and semana (week) are all real time units, but longer periods."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:789d5c27', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘clear’ or ‘light’ (describing a colour or a picture)?", "options": ["claro", "oscuro", "especial", "siguiente"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "claro = clear/light. oscuro (dark) is its direct opposite; especial (special) and siguiente (next) are real adjectives, but different meanings."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:c45b38ba', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘next’ or ‘following’?", "options": ["siguiente", "anterior", "último", "penúltimo"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "siguiente = next/following. anterior (previous), último (last) and penúltimo (second-to-last) are all genuine sequence words that a student can easily mix up."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:067431cb', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘last’ or ‘latest’?", "options": ["último", "siguiente", "especial", "increíble"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "último = last/latest. siguiente (next), especial (special) and increíble (incredible) are real describing words, but different meanings."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:38069159', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘special’?", "options": ["especial", "claro", "siguiente", "increíble"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "especial = special. claro (clear/of course), siguiente (next) and increíble (incredible) are all real adjectives easily confused with it."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:60ec9fed', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘creation’?", "options": ["creación", "creador", "crear", "creativo"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "creación (noun) = creation. creador (creator), crear (to create) and creativo (creative) are the same word family in a different form — a classic part-of-speech mix-up."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:25d69cbe', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which verb means ‘to enter’ or ‘to log into’ (an app)?", "options": ["entrar", "salir", "abrir", "cerrar"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "entrar (en) = to enter/log into. salir (to exit), abrir (to open) and cerrar (to close) are all real related actions, but different ones."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:c2f6e83e', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"Escojo el mejor móvil según el precio.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. What is the person doing?", "options": ["choosing the best phone based on price", "buying the most expensive phone available", "finding a cheap phone online for a friend", "comparing two identical phones before buying"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘escojo el mejor móvil según el precio’ = I choose the best phone according to the price. escoger = to choose, not to buy or compare."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:44025e91', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Complete: ‘La tecnología ___ muy rápido cada año.’ (grows)", "options": ["crece", "creciendo", "crecido", "crecer"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The conjugated present-tense form is needed: crece. creciendo is the gerund, crecido the past participle, crecer the infinitive."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:9c728a11', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which verb means ‘to move’ (e.g. files)?", "options": ["mover", "guardar", "cargar", "borrar"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "mover = to move. guardar (to save), cargar (to charge) and borrar (to delete) are all real device actions, but different ones."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:6d26b507', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Complete: ‘Abro la aplicación y ___ navegando.’ (I continue)", "options": ["continúo", "continuando", "continuado", "continuar"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The conjugated present-tense (yo) form is needed: continúo. The others are the gerund, past participle and infinitive."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:mcq:76025bc9', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which verb means ‘to find’ (the result of searching)?", "options": ["encontrar", "buscar", "descargar", "escoger"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "encontrar = to find. buscar (to search for) is the verb for the action before you find something — a common mix-up; descargar (to download) and escoger (to choose) are unrelated actions."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:tf:194eaa65', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "After ‘para’, the verb always stays as the infinitive."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "para mandar mensajes, para ver vídeos — never conjugated after para."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life:tf:0c7f1632', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-1-technology-in-everyday-life', '8.1 Technology in Everyday Life', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘El móvil’ is a feminine noun, so it should be ‘la móvil’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "móvil is masculine: el móvil, even though many tech words end differently."}'::jsonb),
